 Humansdorp - Detectives from the South African Police Service in Humansdorp are appealing to members of the community to assist in locating a 62-year-old man who was reported missing. "On Friday, 05 June 2020, Jack Oliphant (62) was admitted at the Humansdorp Provincial Hospital, and five days later he disappeared without being formally discharged," said police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "Oliphant was last seen at the hospital on Wednesday, 10 June 2020, and he was wearing hospital clothes. "Anyone with information about his whereabouts is urged to contact the investigating officer, Detective Warrant Officer, Zuan Nepgen, on 082 441 7613 or 081 234 7783." The information may also be shared via Crime Stop 08600 10111 or contact the nearest police station. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 